span>=E2=80=9CNew York, despite its outward chaos, offers a sense of contin=
uity and permanence, in a way that no place from my childhood ever did. It=
=E2=80=99s a city for visionaries, for those who see opportunities and seiz=
e them, or stumble into them.=E2=80=9D</span></p><p><span>Yes, it does. I l=
ived in over a dozen states, two countries, and went to 8 different schools=
 by 8th grade. There was no continuity in my childhood either, but I=E2=80=
=99ve been in lower Manhattan for the last 30+ years. </span></p><p><span>N=
YC is different from everywhere else. It is welcoming somehow in its chaoti=
c anonymity. There are amazing people from all over the planet who are unit=
ed in their attraction to the energy of this place. The City (NYers know th=
ere is only one) calls a certain type of person to come and work here, work=
